SQLite 2.8.17 for RISC OS 3.1
═════════════════════════════

INSTALLATION
────────────

1. Copy the entire !SQLite directory to your applications folder
   Typical locations:
   - !Boot:$.Apps
   - !Boot:$.Applications
   - Your preferred applications directory

2. The application is now ready to use

USAGE
────

From Desktop:
  Double-click on !SQLite icon to launch interactive shell

From Command Line:
  *!Boot:$.Apps.!SQLite.sqlite,ff8
  or
  *SQLite database.db

CONTENTS
────────

!Boot         - Application boot script (sets up memory)
!Run          - Application launcher (executes SQLite)
!Sprites      - Application icons (placeholder)
sqlite,ff8    - SQLite executable (30KB)
README        - This file

FEATURES
────────

✅ Create and manage databases
✅ Interactive SQL shell
✅ Table creation and deletion
✅ Schema viewing
✅ Transaction support
✅ Multiple dot commands (.tables, .schema, .help, etc.)

SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS
──────────────────

- RISC OS 3.1 or later
- ARM2 CPU or compatible
- 4MB RAM minimum
- 1-2MB disk space for application
- Additional space for databases

GETTING STARTED
───────────────

1. Launch SQLite
   - Double-click !SQLite icon, OR
   - Run: *SQLite mydata.db

2. At the prompt, try:
   sqlite> .help           (show all commands)
   sqlite> .tables         (list tables)
   sqlite> CREATE TABLE test (id INTEGER);
   sqlite> .schema         (show schema)
   sqlite> .quit           (exit)

QUICK COMMANDS
──────────────

Database Management:
  .open <file>      - Open database file
  .quit             - Exit SQLite

Table Operations:
  CREATE TABLE      - Create new table
  DROP TABLE        - Delete table
  .tables           - List all tables
  .schema [table]   - Show table schema

Help:
  .help             - Show all commands

Mode Toggling:
  .verbose on|off   - Toggle verbose output
  .headers on|off   - Toggle column headers

LIMITATIONS
──────────

- No concurrent access (single-program only)
- ASCII text only (no Unicode)
- Limited SQL (no triggers, views, subqueries)
- Database size limited by available memory
- Performance depends on ARM2 CPU (~8 MHz)

TROUBLESHOOTING
──────────────

"Cannot open/create database file"
  - Check disk space
  - Verify file path exists
  - Try different directory

"No database open"
  - Use .open command to select database first
  - Or pass database name on command line

"Table already exists"
  - Use different table name, or
  - DROP TABLE first, then CREATE TABLE again

For more help, see documentation files in the main SQLite directory.

